{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Remove/reduce VAT for low/mid-range personal mobile phones & mobile contracts",
        "additional_details": "The Government is requested to introduce VAT Tiers for airtime contracts & phones to recognise the essential nature of these products and to reduce the cost of these products and services to the consumer.\r\n\r\nThe proposed VAT tiers are set out below:\r\n\r\nTier 1: 0%. Contracts <\u00a320/month. Phones <\u00a3200.\r\nTier 2: 5%. Contracts \u00a320-\u00a340/month. Phones \u00a3200-\u00a3500.\r\nTier 3: 20%. Contracts >\u00a340/month. Phones >\u00a3500.\r\n\r\n\u2022 Values raised yearly (greater of RPI & CPI).\r\n\u2022 Top-ups lasting <6 months: zero-rated.\r\n\u2022 Personal devices and contracts only.\r\n\u2022 Bundles considered by component, not total.",
        "background": "Mobile phones are now essential. They're needed for many Government services (HMRC, Track & Trace, the NHS app); online credit card payments & other services.\r\n\r\nThe Government must recognise this by removing & reducing VAT on low/mid-range mobile phones and services.",
